 Now re-issued with a substantial new introduction and concluding reflections, this book provides the only account by key professionals directly involved in the Cleveland cases, allowing readers to understand what really took place in Cleveland and why it continues to matter today. It analyses the many failures to address the plight of sexually abused children and makes constructive suggestions for the way forward to provide more effective interventions for children at risk.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChild sexual abusevCase studiesxInvestigationzEnglandzCleveland. 0aChild sexual abusevCase studieszEnglandzCleveland. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBacon, Heather, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBacon, Heather, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCashman, Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunn, Marjorie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiggs, Marietta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamballe-Armstrong, Annette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, Sue, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWyatt, Geoff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311119666440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447350293423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447350293/original  a978-3-11-119666-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles